      • getPath

        public String getPath()
        Gets the relative path of the asset.

        This method uses '/' as the separator char, and 'assets/objects' as the base dir.
        The asset file is located at: 

         ${mcdir}/assets/objects/${2-character-prefix of hash}/${hash}
        So the format of the return value is: 
         ${2-character-prefix of hash}/${hash}
        Returns:
        the relative path of the asset

      • isValid

        public boolean isValid(MinecraftDirectory dir)
                throws IOException,
                       NoSuchAlgorithmException
        Validates the asset in the given mcdir.

        This method checks the size, hash of the asset. If, one of them mismatches, or the asset file doesn't exist, this method will return false. Or this method will return true.

        Parameters:
        dir - the mcdir where the asset is in
        Returns:
        true if the asset is valid
        Throws:
        IOException - if an i/o error occurs
        NoSuchAlgorithmException - if the default hash algorithm SHA-1 doesn't exist
